Iavan Pijoos, News24(Supplied Netcare911) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Pretoria &ndash; At least 77 people have been injured after two buses collided on Moloto Road in Pretoria on Tuesday morning, paramedics said on Tuesday.Netcare911 spokesperson Athlenda Mathe said all injured people have sustained moderate to minor injuries.Mathe said all of the injured were stabilised and transported to various hospitals in Pretoria.The accident happened at around 08:00 on Tuesday morning.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.